## Summary of Changes Made

### 1. Google Model Prefix Fix (`models/` prefix)
**File**: `src/core/operator/llm-provider-manager.ts`

- **Line ~267**: `GOOGLE_DEFAULT_MODELS` now uses `models/` prefix (e.g. `"models/gemini-2.5-flash"`)
- **Line ~1868-1876**: `getResolvedSettings()` auto-normalizes Google models — any model without `models/` prefix gets it added automatically
- **Why**: Google's OpenAI-compatible endpoint returns 400 "schema constraint" errors when models lack the `models/` prefix

### 2. Thread-Safe Tool Filtering (Race Condition Fix)
**Files**: `llm-provider-manager.ts` + `skills-engine.ts`

- Added `allowedTools?: string[]` to `LlmGenerationInput` interface (line ~199)
- `generate()` (line ~852) and `generateSR()` (line ~1178) now check `input.allowedTools ?? this.temporaryToolFilter`
- `skills-engine.ts`: Removed global `setTemporaryToolFilter()` / `clearTemporaryToolFilter()` calls — now passes `allowedTools` per-request
- **Why**: Global filter was a shared-mutable-state race condition when multiple skill sessions or autonomous goals ran concurrently

### 3. Empty Response Debug Logging
**File**: `llm-provider-manager.ts` (line ~2264)

- When provider returns empty content + no tool calls, logs the full response payload before throwing
- Tagged as `EMPTY_RESPONSE_DEBUG` in `llm-trace.log`

